DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages bash.

The GNU Bourne Again shell (Bash) is a shell or command language interpreter
that is compatible with the Bourne shell (sh). Bash incorporates useful features
from the Korn shell (ksh) and the C shell (csh). Most sh scripts can be run by
bash without modification.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: bash
       bash_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: bash
       bash_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  bash_state
    Specify predetermined 'bash_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'gzip' is a core package and can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

  bash_color_prompt
    Specify predetermined 'bash_color_prompt' variable (string).

    Enable : 'true' | 'yes' | 'enable'
    Disable: 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default: 'enable'

  bash_color_support
    Specify predetermined 'bash_color_support' variable (string).

    Enable : 'true' | 'yes' | 'enable'
    Disable: 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default: 'enable'

  bash_history_readonly
    Specify predetermined 'bash_history_readonly' variable (string).

    Enable : 'true' | 'yes' | 'enable'
    Disable: 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default: 'enable'

  bash_histsize
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_histsize' variable (integer).

    Examples: '32768' | '65536' | '131072' | '262144'
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : '262144'

  bash_histfilesize
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_histfilesize' variable (integer).

    Examples: '32768' | '65536' | '131072' | '262144'
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : '262144'

  bash_histtimeformat
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_histtimeformat' variable (string).

    Examples: '%F %T  '
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : '%F %T  '

  bash_histignore
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_histignore' variable (string).

    Examples: ''
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : ''

  bash_histcontrol
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_histcontrol' variable (string).

    Examples: ''
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : ''

  bash_ls_time_style
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_ls_time_style' variable (string).

    Examples: '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'

  bash_safety
    Specify predetermined 'bash_safety' variable (string).

    Enable : 'true' | 'yes' | 'enable'
    Disable: 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default: 'enable'

  bash_bash_sh_template
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_bash_sh_template' variable (string).
    Any value other than 'main' requires a Jinja2 file to be created.
    The custom Jinja2 file for an example configuration called 'example' needs
    to be placed as follows: 'bash/templates/example/bash.sh.j2'

    Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'
    Default : 'main'

  bash_session_readonly
    Specify predetermined 'bash_session_readonly' variable (string).

    Enable : 'true' | 'yes' | 'enable'
    Disable: 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default: 'enable'

  bash_tmout
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_tmout' variable (integer).

    Examples: '300' | '600' | '1200' | '1800'
    Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
    Default : '1800'

  bash_z_bash_sh_template
    Specify arbitrary 'bash_z_bash_sh_template' variable (string).
    Any value other than 'main' requires a Jinja2 file to be created.
    The custom Jinja2 file for an example configuration called 'example' needs
    to be placed as follows: 'bash/templates/example/z_bash.sh.j2'

    Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'
    Default : 'main'

